PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F303A1775682667
OL,3,CChurch of England to apologise for
OL,4,Crole in historical forced adoptions
OL,6,FIn post-war Britain an estimated
OL,7,F250,000 unmarried women were sent to
OL,8,Finstitutions run by religious
OL,9,Forganisations - including the Church
OL,10,Fof England - and the state, where they
OL,11,Fwere pressured and coerced to put
OL,12,Ftheir babies up for adoption between
OL,13,Fthe 1940s and 1980s. Other infants
OL,14,Fdied through poor care.
OL,16,FThe Church of England operated and
OL,17,Ffunded 107 mother and baby homes and
OL,18,Fhad over 30 adoption agencies.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/15
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
