PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F303A1775682667
OL,3,CChurch of England to apologise for
OL,4,Crole in historical forced adoptions
OL,6,FIn a draft seen by ITV News, the
OL,7,FChurch apologises "for the pain and
OL,8,Ftrauma experienced ` and still carried
OL,9,F- by many women and children in Church-
OL,10,Faffiliated mother and baby homes."
OL,12,FIt continues: "We acknowledge the
OL,13,Flifelong impact of these experiences
OL,14,Fand the part the Church played in a
OL,15,Fsystem - shaped by attitudes and
OL,16,Fbehaviours that we now recognise as
OL,17,Fharmful."
OL,26,@oD@SOUtD@OOUyD@IO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/15
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,304,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30304
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F303A1775682667
OL,3,CChurch of England to apologise for
OL,4,Crole in historical forced adoptions
OL,6,F"Where our words or actions fell short
OL,7,Fof what a Christian community should
OL,8,Fembody, we feel sorrow and shame, and
OL,9,Fwe apologise to all those who have
OL,10,Fbeen hurt."
OL,12,FDr Michael Lambert, from Lancaster
OL,13,FUniversity, who has spent a decade
OL,14,Fexamining these institutions, said the
OL,15,FChurch of England was the significant
OL,16,Fplayer in historical forced adoptions,
OL,17,Fsecond only to the state.
OL,26,@nD@AOUrD@KO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/15
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,304,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30305
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F303A1775682667
OL,3,CChurch of England to apologise for
OL,4,Crole in historical forced adoptions
OL,6,F"It ran the most homes, it had the
OL,7,Fmost adoption agencies, it was the
OL,8,Fcentral institution of the time," he
OL,9,Ftold ITV News.
OL,11,F"I think, particularly for those
OL,12,Fmothers, hearing an apology from the
OL,13,Fchurch would perhaps mean more than
OL,14,Fone coming from the state.
OL,16,F"Bearing in mind the strong religious
OL,17,Fconnotations - ideas of sin, of shame,
OL,18,Fof having transgressed. Lots of people
OL,19,Fwould have lived with these and
OL,20,Finternalised these for their entire
OL,21,Flives.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/15
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
