OL,3,CChurch of England to apologise for
OL,4,Crole in historical forced adoptions
OL,6,FITV News understands that the Church
OL,7,Fof England has been working with
OL,8,Fsurvivor groups on the wording of this
OL,9,Fapology since last year, a process
OL,10,Fbeing co-ordinated by Bishop Joanne
OL,11,FGrenfell, the Church's safeguarding
OL,12,Flead.
OL,14,FThe Archbishop of Canterbury is also
OL,15,Ftaking a close, personal interest, we
OL,16,Fhave been told.
OL,18,FAll of this will only increase
OL,19,Fpressure on the government to also
OL,20,Fformally acknowledge its role in these
OL,21,Fcruel practices.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G7/15
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,304,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30308
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F303A1775682667
OL,3,CChurch of England to apologise for
OL,4,Crole in historical forced adoptions
OL,6,FThis is a significant moment for
OL,7,Fsurvivors. Many have been campaigning
OL,8,Ffor decades for the church and state
OL,9,Fto be open and transparent about the
OL,10,Ftrauma they endured.
OL,12,FThe campaign group the Adult Adoptee
OL,13,FMovement welcomed the Church of
OL,14,FEngland's intention to apologise but
OL,15,Fsaid it is "essential that any apology
OL,16,Fis preceded by a full consultation
OL,17,Fwith mother and adult adoptee
OL,18,Fsurvivors" to understand the damage
OL,19,Fdone.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G8/15
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,304,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30309
SC,0009
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F303A1775682667
OL,3,CChurch of England to apologise for
OL,4,Crole in historical forced adoptions
OL,6,F"It is also important that it
OL,7,Frecognises the full scale of the
OL,8,FChurch's involvement," the statement
OL,9,Fcontinued. "The Church must work with
OL,10,Fsurvivors on a package of appropriate
OL,11,Fsupport measures."
OL,13,FToday's development will add more
OL,14,Fpressure on the government.
OL,16,FLast week, Sir Keir Starmer said his
OL,17,F"instinct" is to issue a government
OL,18,Fapology for the state's role in the
OL,19,Fforced adoption scandal, in an
OL,20,Fexclusive interview with ITV News.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G9/15
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,304,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30310
SC,0010
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F303A1775682667
OL,3,CChurch of England to apologise for
OL,4,Crole in historical forced adoptions
OL,6,FThe prime minister admitted "my own
OL,7,Fview is there is a very strong case
OL,8,Ffor an apology", adding that he wants
OL,9,Fto make sure the government involves
OL,10,Fsurvivors in the process.
OL,12,F"I've asked the teams to speed up what
OL,13,Fwe're doing, I want to get this right
OL,14,Fwith the campaigners and all those
OL,15,Faffected," he added.
OL,17,FThe same day a cross-party committee
OL,18,Fof MPs said that the government must
OL,19,Fissue a formal, unqualified apology to
OL,20,Fsurvivors of forced adoption who have
OL,21,F"suffered for too long".
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G10/15
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,304,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30311
SC,0011
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F303A1775682667
OL,3,CChurch of England to apologise for
OL,4,Crole in historical forced adoptions
OL,6,FThe practice caused "unimaginable
OL,7,Ftrauma" for generations of women and
OL,8,Fleft "profound, often devastating
OL,9,Fimpacts" on their children, the Chair
OL,10,Fof the Education Committee, Helen
OL,11,FHayes, said.
OL,13,FThe committee has called for the
OL,14,Fgovernment to commit to an apology for
OL,15,Fthe state's role in the scandal, with
OL,16,FMPs saying the matter must be treated
OL,17,Fwith urgency "given the advancing age
OL,18,Fof those affected".
