CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F303A1775682667
OL,3,CChurch of England to apologise for
OL,4,Crole in historical forced adoptions
OL,6,FITV News' years-long investigation
OL,7,Finto the forced adoption scandal has
OL,8,Falready revealed hundreds of unmarked
OL,9,Fgraves of babies born in state and
OL,10,Fchurch-run homes across England, with
OL,11,Fallegations that sick or premature
OL,12,Fchildren were left to die as they
OL,13,Fweren't deemed "desirable" for
OL,14,Fadoption.
OL,16,FLast year, we revealed nearly 200
OL,17,Finfants who died at eight mother and
OL,18,Fbaby homes are buried in mass plots in
OL,19,Ften different cemeteries across
OL,20,FEngland.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G13/15
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,304,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30314
SC,0014
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F303A1775682667
OL,3,CChurch of England to apologise for
OL,4,Crole in historical forced adoptions
OL,6,FTo this day, families are still
OL,7,Fsearching for their lost children
OL,8,Fconnected to these post-war
OL,9,Finstitutions.
OL,11,FA government spokesperson previously
OL,12,Ftold ITV News: "This abhorrent
OL,13,Fpractice should never have taken
OL,14,Fplace, and our deepest sympathies are
OL,15,Fwith all those affected.
OL,17,F"We take this issue extremely
OL,18,Fseriously and continue to engage with
OL,19,Fthose affected to provide support."
OL,26,@tD@POUyD@AOU{D@cO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G14/15
